'''Arborsculpture''' is a branch of [[Arboriculture]] specifically involved with the shaping of trees into structures with ornamental or functional utility. 
[[Image:Pretzel Tree.gif|frame|right|Pretzel Tree By Aharon Naveh - Israel]] 
Naturally occurring arborsculptural events are termed [[Inosculation]]. The art of arborsculpture, as practiced primarily in Europe for many years and restricted to the man-made inosculation of living branches is called [[pleaching]]. Although pleaching dates farthest back, it is only one of several techniques used to shape trees.
The term Arborsculpture was coined in the 1990's but the practice can be dated back thousands of years.

